{
  "texts": [
    "F1 score shows the highest steepness, F β score with β = 2 next, and F β score with β = 0.5 shows the least steepness.",
    "Apparently, F-scores have a monotonically increasing relationship with prevalence, which is verified by a simple mathematical derivation for F1 score shown in Appendix B.",
    "Similarly, both Falkes-Mallows index and Jaccard index show a monotonically increasing relationship with prevalence.",
    "From Eqs 6 and 8 in section 2.2, we know that both metrics are close to PPV in form, therefore, it is unsurprising that both metrics show a similarly downtown trend as PPV though with more steepness.",
    "It can be observed that accuracy has a convex curve with respect to prevalence, that is accuracy has lower values when prevalence is around 0.5 while it has higher values when prevalence goes to either the upper or lower extremes."
  ]
}